     8в†’# Structs
    10в†’Structs contains various utilities to work with Go (Golang) structs. It was
    11в†’initially used by me to convert a struct into a `map[string]interface{}`. With
    12в†’time I've added other utilities for structs.  It's basically a high level
    13в†’package based on primitives from the reflect package. Feel free to add new
    14в†’functions or improve the existing code.
    15в†’
    16в†’## Install
    18в†’```bash
    19в†’go get github.com/fatih/structs
    20в†’```
    21в†’
    22в†’## Usage and Examples
    24в†’Just like the standard lib `strings`, `bytes` and co packages, `structs` has
    25в†’many global functions to manipulate or organize your struct data. Lets define
    26в†’and declare a struct:
    27в†’
    28в†’```go
    29в†’type Server struct {
    30в†’	Name        string `json:"name,omitempty"`
    31в†’	ID          int
    32в†’	Enabled     bool
    33в†’	users       []string // not exported
    34в†’	http.Server          // embedded
    35в†’}
    36в†’
    37в†’server := &Server{
    38в†’	Name:    "gopher",
    39в†’	ID:      123456,
    40в†’	Enabled: true,
    41в†’}
    42в†’```
    43в†’
    44в†’```go
      в†’вЂ¦
    74в†’### Struct methods
    76в†’The structs functions can be also used as independent methods by creating a new
    77в†’`*structs.Struct`. This is handy if you want to have more control over the
    78в†’structs (such as retrieving a single Field).
    79в†’
    80в†’```go
